# Linting Discipline

- Do not use `eslint-disable`, `eslint-disable-next-line`, or file-level disable blocks.
- Do not suppress TypeScript diagnostics with `// @ts-ignore`.
- Resolve the root cause of lint/type errors instead of muting rules.
- Run `pnpm lint` after edits and address all new issues.
- Keep lint config changes rare and justify them in the change description.
